<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: 3dfx emulator...any out there that work?</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?The RealmWeaver">The RealmWeaver</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 10:23 p.m. 10/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: 3dfx emulator...any out there that work?<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=677" TARGET=_self>3dfx emulator...any out there that work?</A> (Tarquin)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>I have never heard of a 3dfx emulator, the reason the ones you have are a joke is probably because ALL of them are a joke. The function of a 3dfx card is to take the load off of your central processor for rendering 3d graphics because a regular video card and processor cannot deal with the advanced graphics in 3dfx ( trilinear mipmapping, dual-texture pixels, pixel dithering, etc.) So the whole idea of an emulator is defunct, it just isn't possible and I wouldn't count on it.

<P>&gt; if its for any help i currently got matrox millenium w/4mb wram
<BR>&gt; , 400a celeron..etc so i got enough cpu and memory (128) to run
<BR>&gt; without 3d card ...I played other games without hardware 3d
<BR>&gt; accelerator and they worked fine..(in lower resolutions up to
<BR>&gt; 640x480)..so why can't i do same for everquest?
<P>Because Everquest REQUIRES a 3dfx card - most games just recommend them.
<P>&gt; Let me know if something can be done to sorta go around "No
<BR>&gt; 3D card detected" message :P
<P>No. And on a side note, why did you purchase a 2d/3d card if you need 3dfx and already have a 2d card? The only 2d/3d card on the market that comes close to the performance of pure 3dfx cards is the Voodoo Banshee, but why go with it if you already have the Matrox?! My advice to you: during beta test, send out for a Voodoo1 or Voodoo2 or Riva TNT card and return your 2d/3d card when it arrives.
<P>[The RealmWeaver]
<P>dcc5500@rit.edu
<BR>ICQ#: 30795819
<BR>IM: WrldWeaver
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
